    </author>
    <author initials="P. R." surname="Calhoun" fullname="Pat R. Calhoun"/>
    <date day="01" month="July" year="1999"/>
    <abstract>
      <t>The use of possibly non-unique private addresses (i.e., addresses
that are not globally routable in the internet) for mobile nodes,
foreign agents, or home agents is not handled by RFC 2002.  This
document specifies changes to enable Mobile IP to handle such
addresses.</t>
    </abstract>
  </front>
